# **Part 2**

## **Describe something that helped you learn a foreign language.**

One thing that has helped me tremendously in learning a foreign language is actually YouTube, especially English-learning channels and interview videos. Although it may sound quite ordinary, I genuinely think it changed the way I learn languages.

The foreign language I’ve been learning is English. I started taking it seriously when I entered university because I realized that English is extremely important for my future career, especially since I’m studying computer science and I hope to work in the AI field one day. A lot of cutting-edge research papers, lectures, and technical resources are written in English, so I felt that improving my language skills was almost unavoidable.

The reason I chose YouTube as a learning tool is that traditional textbooks sometimes feel a bit dull and disconnected from real-life communication. On YouTube, however, I can hear authentic pronunciation, natural expressions, and even different accents from around the world. For example, I often watch IELTS speaking videos, podcasts, tech interviews, and even vlogs from international students.

What helped me most was the combination of listening and visual context. Even if I didn’t understand every word at first, I could still guess the meaning through facial expressions, subtitles, and the situation in the video. Gradually, my listening skills improved a lot, and I became more confident speaking English aloud.

Another advantage is that YouTube made language learning feel enjoyable rather than stressful. Instead of forcing myself to memorize vocabulary lists for hours, I could learn naturally while watching topics I was genuinely interested in, such as artificial intelligence, programming, or productivity.

To be honest, I think consistency is the key to language learning, and YouTube helped me stay consistent because it turned learning into part of my daily entertainment. Even now, I still use it almost every day to improve my English.

---

## **中文翻译：**

帮助我学习外语的一样东西其实是 YouTube，尤其是一些英语学习频道和访谈视频。虽然听起来很普通，但我真的觉得它改变了我学习语言的方式。

我学习的外语是英语。我是在进入大学后开始认真学习英语的，因为我意识到英语对我未来的职业发展非常重要。尤其是我学的是计算机科学，而且未来希望从事 AI 相关领域。很多前沿论文、课程以及技术资料都是英文的，所以提高英语几乎是不可避免的事情。

我之所以选择 YouTube 作为学习工具，是因为传统教材有时候会比较枯燥，而且和真实交流有些脱节。但在 YouTube 上，我可以听到地道发音、自然表达，甚至世界各地不同的口音。比如我经常看雅思口语视频、播客、科技访谈，还有一些国际学生的 vlog。

对我帮助最大的是“听觉+视觉”的结合。即使一开始我听不懂每一个词，我仍然可以通过表情、字幕以及视频情境去猜测意思。慢慢地，我的听力提升了很多，说英语时也更加自信了。

另一个优点是，YouTube 让语言学习变得更有趣，而不是一种压力。相比强迫自己背单词，我可以在观看自己真正感兴趣的话题时自然地学习，比如人工智能、编程或者效率提升。

说实话，我觉得语言学习最重要的是坚持，而 YouTube 帮助我保持了这种持续性，因为它让学习变成了我日常娱乐的一部分。直到现在，我几乎每天都还在用它提升英语。

